<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1228,1397]" box="[199,565,1263,1288]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
Previous Reports: 
<bibRefCitation author="Alfken" box="[406,565,1263,1288]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" refString="Alfken, J. D. (1929) Ueber eine Hymenopteren-Ausbeute von Malta. Mitteilungen der Entomologischen Verein, 15 - 17, 9 - 11." type="book chapter" year="1929">Alfken (1929)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1228,1397]" box="[199,907,1300,1325]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
Distribution: West Mediterranean Basin, 
<collectingRegion box="[659,747,1300,1325]" country="France" name="Corse" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<collectingCountry box="[659,747,1300,1325]" name="France" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Corsica</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[806,903,1300,1325]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1228,1397]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1306553831" country="Malta" location="Sicily" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Sicily">
<taxonomicName box="[199,377,1336,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricornis">
<emphasis box="[199,377,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Osmia tricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has often been confounded with closely related 
<taxonomicName box="[935,1035,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Osmia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kohlii">
<emphasis box="[935,1035,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">O. kohlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[1242,1307,1335,1360]" name="Malta" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Malta</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1366,1433,1335,1360]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Sicily</collectingRegion>
. However, these two species show an allopatric distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Muller" box="[824,976,1372,1397]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" refString="Muller, A. (2015) Palaearctic Osmiine Bees, ETH Zurich. Available from: http: // blogs. ethz. ch / osmiini (accessed 16 February 2016)" type="journal article" year="2015">Müller, 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1444,1648]" box="[151,588,1444,1469]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1793" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[151,588,1444,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,389,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Megachile argentata</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1793)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1444,1648]" box="[199,573,1479,1504]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1306553825" box="[199,573,1479,1504]" location="Valletta" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Valletta">
Previous Reports: 
<bibRefCitation author="Valletta" box="[406,573,1479,1504]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" refString="Valletta, A. (1971) A preliminary list of the Hymenoptera Aculeata (excluding ants) of the Maltese Islands. Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 107, 45 - 46." type="journal article" year="1971">
