(1971)
</bibRefCitation>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1444,1648]" box="[199,545,1516,1541]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
Distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[349,436,1516,1541]" name="Algeria" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[447,545,1517,1541]" name="Hungary" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Hungary</collectingCountry>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1444,1648]" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">
The species 
<taxonomicName box="[341,489,1553,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentata">
<emphasis box="[341,489,1553,1576]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">M. argentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has often been confounded with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Curtis, 1828) (Schwarz and Gusenleitner 2011)" authorityName="(Curtis, 1828) (Schwarz and Gusenleitner" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leachella">
<emphasis box="[873,1103,1551,1576]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">Megachile leachella</emphasis>
(Curtis, 1828) (
<bibRefCitation author="Schwarz" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" refString="Schwarz, M. Gusdenleitner, F. (2011) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Gattung Megachile (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Megachilinae). Entomofauna Zeitschrift Fur Entomologie, 32, 249 - 260." type="journal article" year="2011">Schwarz and Gusenleitner 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter has not been recorded from the Maltese Islands. 
<taxonomicName box="[1134,1279,1588,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leachella">
<emphasis box="[1134,1279,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="238">M. leachella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present in Continental Europe and North Africa.
</paragraph>
